(varchar 20, nullable)\n  - `message` (text, NOT NULL, 10-2000 chars)\n  - `status` (enum InquiryStatusEnum, default 'new')\n  - `response` (text, nullable)\n  - `responded_at` (timestamp, nullable)\n  - **Note (line 380)**: Soft delete NOT enabled on `inquiries` — \"retained indefinitely for audit\"\n- **Relationships (lines 271-272)**: belongsTo Property, belongsTo User\n\n### 2d. User → Inquiry relationship\n- **File**: `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/modules/users/entities/user.entity.ts`\n- **Lines 60-61**: `@OneToMany(() => Inquiry, (inquiry) => inquiry.user)` — `inquiries: Inquiry[]`\n\n### 2e. Property → Inquiry relationship\n- **File**: `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/modules/properties/entities/property.entity.ts`\n- **Lines 78-79**: `@OneToMany(() => Inquiry, (inquiry) => inquiry.property)` — `inquiries: Inquiry[]`\n\n### 2f. Admin Dashboard → Inquiry usage\n- **File**: `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/modules/admin/admin.service.ts`\n- **Lines 10, 22-23**: Imports `Inquiry` entity and injects `inquiryRepo`.\n- **Lines 28-75**: `getDashboardStats()` — counts total inquiries, new inquiries, fetches recent 5.\n- **Lines 169-171**: `getUserDetail()` — counts user's total inquiries.\n\n### 2g. Database Migration (Inquiry table)\n- **File**: `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/database/migrations/001-initial-schema.ts`\n- **Lines 239-256**: Creates `inquiries` table with all columns and defaults.\n- **Lines 258-261**: Creates indexes on `property_id`, `user_id`, `status`, `[status, created_at]`.\n- **Lines 263-281**: Creates foreign keys with `ON DELETE SET NULL`.\n\n### 2h. PROJECT_API.md — Inquiries API section\n- **File**: `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/docs/PROJECT_API.md`\n- **Lines 816-1034**: Full API documentation for inquiries.\n- **API Endpoints defined**:\n  | Method | Path | Description | Auth |\n  |--------|------|-------------|------|\n  | POST | `/api/inquiries` | Submit an inquiry | User (Renter) |\n  | GET | `/api/inquiries` | List all inquiries (with filters) | Admin |\n  | GET | `/api/inquiries/:id` | Get inquiry detail | Admin |\n  | PATCH | `/api/inquiries/:id/status` | Update inquiry status | Admin |\n  | POST | `/api/inquiries/:id/respond` | Respond to an inquiry | Admin |\n\n**CRITICAL**: The API doc says `POST /api/inquiries` (line 820), but the test file `inquiries.e2e-spec.ts` uses `POST /api/properties/:id/inquiries`. The controller has `POST /inquiries` (no property ID in path). There is a **mismatch between the API contract, tests, and the implementation**.\n\n### 2i. App Module Registration\n- **File**: `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/app.module.ts`\n- **Line 8**: `import { InquiryModule } from './modules/inquiries/inquiry.module'`\n- **Line 29**: `InquiryModule` registered in imports array.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Test Files Under `backend/test/` Targeting Inquiries\n\n### 3a. `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/test/e2e/inquiries.e2e-spec.ts` (499 lines)\n- Full E2E test suite for inquiries.\n- **Lines 15-16**: Comment noting \"RED PHASE\" — imports expected to fail because modules don't exist yet (but they DO exist now).\n- **Line 13**: Imports `Inquiry` entity.\n- **Uses**: `createTestApp()`, `closeTestApp()`, `cleanDatabase()`, `seedTestUsers()`, `seedTestProperties()`, `generateAccessToken()`, `authHeader()`.\n\n**Test endpoints tested (with expected behaviors)**:\n\n| Test Section | Method | Path | Lines | Auth | Tests |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Submit Inquiry | `POST` | `/api/properties/:id/inquiries` | 52-161 | Renter only | 10 tests: 201, denormalization, override fields, 400 (missing/long msg), 400 (invalid UUID), 401, 403 (admin), 404 (property not found) |\n| List All | `GET` | `/api/inquiries` | 164-280 | Admin only | 8 tests: 200 + pagination meta, correct shape (property/renter nested), status filter, propertyId filter, search, sorting, pagination, 401, 403 (renter) |\n| Detail | `GET` | `/api/inquiries/:id` | 283-343 | Admin only | 5 tests: 200, 400 (invalid UUID), 401, 403 (renter), 404 |\n| Mark Read | `PATCH` | `/api/inquiries/:id/read` | 346-412 | Admin only | 6 tests: 200, 400 (invalid UUID), 401, 403, 404, 400 (already read/responded) |\n| Respond | `POST` | `/api/inquiries/:id/respond` | 415-498 | Admin only | 8 tests: 200, 400 (missing/short/long/invalid UUID), 401, 403, 404 |\n\n**Key test expectations that the current implementation should match:**\n- POST submit returns 201 with `success: true`, `statusCode: 201`, `message: 'Inquiry submitted successfully'`\n- Response shape: `{ success, statusCode, message, data: { id, propertyId, name, email, phone, message, status, response, respondedAt, createdAt } }`\n- Message validation: 10-2000 chars (for inquiry), 10-5000 chars (for response)\n- `GET /api/inquiries` response: `{ items[], meta: { total, page, limit, totalPages } }`\n- Items in list include `property: { id, title }` and `renter: { id, name, email }` (but entity uses `user` not `renter`)\n- Status filter supports `?status=new`\n- Search supports `?search=<query>`\n- Sorting supports `?sortBy=newest`\n\n### 3b. `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/test/e2e/inquiries-my.e2e-spec.ts` (269 lines)\n- Tests a **missing endpoint**: `GET /api/inquiries/my`.\n- **Lines 17-21**: Comment explicitly marking this as a MISSING ENDPOINT from MISSING_ENDPOINTS.yaml.\n- Tests require renter to see only their own inquiries (not admin's all-inquiry view).\n\n**Tests for this missing endpoint:**\n| Test | Method | Path | Lines | Expected |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| List own inquiries | `GET` | `/api/inquiries/my` | 63-102 | 200 with `{ items[], meta: { total, page, limit, totalPages } }` |\n| Correct shape | `GET` | `/api/inquiries/my` | 104-125 | property.id, property.title, name, email, phone, message, status, response, respondedAt, createdAt |\n| Only own inquiries | `GET` | `/api/inquiries/my` | 127-141 | Total = 2, all items have renter's email |\n| Not others' inquiries | `GET` | `/api/inquiries/my` | 143-151 | Messages don't contain renter2's inquiry |\n| Empty results | `GET` | `/api/inquiries/my` | 153-171 | items=[], total=0 for fresh user |\n| Pagination | `GET` | `/api/inquiries/my?page=1&limit=1` | 173-183 | Correct page/limit/total |\n| Sorting | `GET` | `/api/inquiries/my?sortBy=newest` | 185-192 | 200 |\n| 400 invalid params | `GET` | `/api/inquiries/my?limit=9999` | 194-199 | 400 |\n| 401 unauthenticated | `GET` | `/api/inquiries/my` | 201-205 | 401 |\n| 401 invalid token | `GET` | `/api/inquiries/my` | 207-212 | 401 with invalid token header |\n| 403 admin | `GET` | `/api/inquiries/my` | 214-219 | 403 for admin |\n| Response data visible | `GET` | `/api/inquiries/my` | 221-251 | Responded inquiry shows status='responded', response, respondedAt |\n| Property title | `GET` | `/api/inquiries/my` | 253-266 | property.title exists, property IDs match |\n\n---\n\n## 4. MISSING_ENDPOINTS.yaml About Inquiries\n\n**File**: `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/status/MISSING_ENDPOINTS.yaml` (29 lines)\n\nFull content:\n```yaml\ngenerated_at: \"2026-05-19T20:00:00.000Z\"\ngen: 1\ntotal_pages: 22\nwired_pages: 17\nskipped_pages: 0\nmissing_endpoints:\n  - resource: inquiries\n    module_name: inquiries\n    reason: >\n      GET /inquiries is admin-only per API contract, but renter/inquiries.tsx\n      needs the authenticated renter's own inquiries. Either scoping GET /inquiries\n      by role (admin→all, renter→own) or add a dedicated renter endpoint.\n    suggested_routes:\n      - method: GET\n        path: /inquiries\n        description: >\n          List inquiries — admin sees all; renter sees their own.\n          If scoping by role is undesirable, add a separate /inquiries/my endpoint.\n        scope: worker\n        response_shape: { items: InquiryDto[], meta: PaginationMeta }\n      - method: GET\n        path: /inquiries/my\n        description: List inquiries submitted by the authenticated renter (dedicated endpoint)\n        scope: renter\n        response_shape: { items: InquiryDto[], meta: PaginationMeta }\n    consuming_pages:\n      - frontend/app/pages/renter/inquiries.tsx\n```\n\n**Interpretation**: The frontend `renter/inquiries.tsx` needs to list the current renter's own inquiries. The API contract specifies `GET /inquiries` is admin-only. Two solutions were suggested:\n1. Scope `GET /inquiries` by role (admin → all, renter → own)\n2. Add a dedicated `GET /inquiries/my` endpoint.\n\nThe current controller implements **option 1** (role-based scoping in the `findAll` handler, lines 27-33), but the test file `inquiries.e2e-spec.ts` expects `GET /inquiries` to be admin-only (403 for renters). And `inquiries-my.e2e-spec.ts` tests the dedicated `/my` path. So there is a **conflict between the current implementation and what tests expect**.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Base Class Signatures (`backend/src/core/base/`)\n\nAll files at `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/base/`:\n\n### 5a. `base.entity.ts` (20 lines)\n```typescript\nexport abstract class BaseEntity {\n    @PrimaryGeneratedColumn('uuid')    id: string;\n    @CreateDateColumn({ name: 'created_at', type: 'datetime' })    createdAt: Date;\n    @UpdateDateColumn({ name: 'updated_at', type: 'datetime' })    updatedAt: Date;\n    @DeleteDateColumn({ name: 'deleted_at', type: 'datetime', nullable: true })    deletedAt: Date | null;\n}\n```\n\n### 5b. `base.repository.ts` (53 lines)\n```typescript\nexport abstract class BaseRepository<T extends BaseEntity> {\n    constructor(protected readonly repository: Repository<T>) {}\n    async findAll(options?: FindManyOptions<T>): Promise<T[]>\n    async findById(id: string, relations?: FindOptionsRelations<T>): Promise<T | null>\n    async findOne(options: FindOneOptions<T>): Promise<T | null>\n    async create(data: DeepPartial<T>): Promise<T>\n    async update(id: string, data: DeepPartial<T>): Promise<T | null>\n    async softDelete(id: string): Promise<void>\n    async delete(id: string): Promise<void>\n    async count(options?: FindManyOptions<T>): Promise<number>\n}\n```\n\n### 5c. `base.service.ts` (57 lines)\n```typescript\nexport abstract class BaseService<T extends BaseEntity> {\n    constructor(protected readonly repository: BaseRepository<T>, protected readonly entityName: string) {}\n    protected defaultRelations?: FindOptionsRelations<T>;\n    async findByIdOrFail(id: string, relations?: FindOptionsRelations<T>): Promise<T>\n    async findAll(options?: FindManyOptions<T>): Promise<T[]>\n    async create(data: DeepPartial<T>): Promise<T>\n    async update(id: string, data: DeepPartial<T>): Promise<T | null>\n    async remove(id: string): Promise<void>\n    async delete(id: string): Promise<void>\n}\n```\n\n### 5d. `base.controller.ts` (86 lines)\n```typescript\nexport abstract class BaseController<T extends BaseEntity, CreateDto extends DeepPartial<T> = DeepPartial<T>, UpdateDto extends DeepPartial<T> = DeepPartial<T>> {\n    constructor(protected readonly service: BaseService<T>) {}\n    @Post()  @HttpCode(HttpStatus.CREATED)  async create(@Body() createDto: CreateDto): Promise<T>\n    @Get()   @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)       async findAll(@Query('page') page?, @Query('limit') limit?): Promise<T[]>\n    @Get(':id')  @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)  async findOne(@Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id): Promise<T>\n    @Patch(':id') @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK) async update(@Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id, @Body() updateDto): Promise<T | null>\n    @Delete(':id') @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK) async remove(@Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id): Promise<void>\n}\n```\nIncludes Swagger decorators (`@ApiOperation`, `@ApiResponse`, `@ApiParam`, `@ApiQuery`).\n\n### 5e. `index.ts` (4 lines)\nRe-exports: `BaseEntity`, `BaseRepository`, `BaseService`, `BaseController`.\n\n**KEY FINDING**: The `InquiryService` does NOT extend `BaseService`, `InquiryController` does NOT extend `BaseController`, and there is no `InquiryRepository` extending `BaseRepository`. This violates the project's \"ALL layers extend base classes\" convention stated in CLAUDE.md.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Patterns from Other Feature Modules\n\n### 6a. Properties Module (most complete, good reference)\n| File | Extends | Notes |\n|------|---------|-------|\n| `property.controller.ts` | None (plain class) | Uses `@Roles('admin')` and `@Public()` |\n| `property.service.ts` | `BaseService<Property>` | Constructor: `super(propertyRepository, 'Property')` |\n| `property.repository.ts` | `BaseRepository<Property>` | Constructor: `super(repository)` |\n| `property.module.ts` | — | Registers repository as a provider |\n\n**Pattern**: Uses separate Repository → Service → Controller layers. Service extends `BaseService`, Repository extends `BaseRepository`.\n\n### 6b. Users Module\n| File | Extends | Notes |\n|------|---------|-------|\n| `user.service.ts` | `BaseService<User>` | Constructor: `super(userRepository, 'User')` |\n| `user.repository.ts` | `BaseRepository<User>` | Constructor: `super(repository)` |\n| `user.module.ts` | — | Registers repository + service, exports service |\n\n### 6c. Favorites Module (best match for inquiries pattern)\n| File | Extends | Notes |\n|------|---------|-------|\n| `favorite.controller.ts` | None | Uses `@Controller('favorites')`, `@UseGuards(RolesGuard)` at class level, `@Roles('renter')` per endpoint, Swagger decorators |\n| `favorite.service.ts` | `BaseService<Favorite>` | Has additional methods: `add()`, `removeByPropertyId()`, `findByUser()`, `isFavorited()` |\n| `favorite.repository.ts` | `BaseRepository<Favorite>` | Has custom methods: `findByUserIdWithProperty()`, `findByUserAndProperty()` |\n| `favorite.module.ts` | — | Imports `TypeOrmModule.forFeature([Favorite, Property])` |\n| `favorite.controller.ts` response format | — | Returns `{ success: true, statusCode, message, data: { items, meta: { total, page, limit, totalPages } } }` |\n\n### 6d. Auth Module\n| File | Extends | Notes |\n|------|---------|-------|\n| `auth.controller.ts` | None | Full Swagger decorators, response format: `{ success, statusCode, message, data, timestamp, path }` |\n| `auth.service.ts` | None | Not CRUD-based — handles JWT/auth logic |\n| `auth.module.ts` | — | Complex setup with JWT, Passport, config |\n\n**Pattern summary for CRUD resources (properties, users, favorites):**\n1. **Entity** → `extends BaseEntity`\n2. **Repository** → `extends BaseRepository<T>` (custom query methods go here)\n3. **Service** → `extends BaseService<T>` (business logic goes here)\n4. **Controller** → plain class (does NOT extend BaseController, but could)\n5. **Module** → registers: `[Entity]` in `forFeature`, `[Repository, Service]` as providers, `[Controller]` as controllers\n6. **DTOs** → in `dto/` directory with `class-validator` decorators\n\n---\n\n## 7. Module Directory Structure (`backend/src/modules/`)\n\n```\nbackend/src/modules/\n├── admin/         (4 entries: admin.controller.ts, admin.module.ts, admin.service.ts, dtos/)\n├── amenities/     (5 entries: amenity.controller.ts, amenity.module.ts, amenity.repository.ts, amenity.service.ts, dto/)\n├── auth/          (5 entries: auth.controller.ts, auth.module.ts, dto/, entities/, services/)\n├── favorites/     (6 entries: favorite.controller.ts, favorite.module.ts, favorite.repository.ts, favorite.service.ts, dto/, entities/)\n├── inquiries/     (5 entries: inquiry.controller.ts, inquiry.module.ts, inquiry.service.ts, dto/, entities/)\n├── properties/    (6 entries: property.controller.ts, property.module.ts, property.repository.ts, property.service.ts, dto/, entities/)\n└── users/         (5 entries: user.module.ts, user.repository.ts, user.service.ts, dto/, entities/)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary: Critical Issues and Gaps in the Inquiries Module\n\n1. **Missing `GET /inquiries/my` endpoint**: Tested in `inquiries-my.e2e-spec.ts`, consumed by `frontend/app/pages/renter/inquiries.tsx`, documented in `MISSING_ENDPOINTS.yaml`. Not yet implemented in the controller.\n\n2. **`POST /inquiries` vs `POST /properties/:id/inquiries` mismatch**: The API doc says `POST /api/inquiries`, the test expects `POST /api/properties/:id/inquiries`, the controller has `POST /inquiries` (no propertyId in path, no validation of propertyId).\n\n3. **No base class inheritance**: `InquiryService` does NOT extend `BaseService`, `InquiryController` does NOT extend `BaseController`, and there is NO `InquiryRepository` extending `BaseRepository`. This violates the project convention.\n\n4. **No DTO files**: `dto/` directory is empty. No `CreateInquiryDto`, `SubmitInquiryDto`, `RespondToInquiryDto`, etc. Tests expect validation (min/max message length, required fields).\n\n5. **`softDelete` used incorrectly**: `PROJECT_DATABASE.md` line 380 states soft delete is NOT enabled on `inquiries` (retained indefinitely for audit), but the service and entity DO have soft delete (the entity extends `BaseEntity` which has `@DeleteDateColumn`).\n\n6. **No `@UseGuards(RolesGuard)` at class level**: Unlike the favorites controller which has it at class level, the inquiry controller applies `@Roles('admin')` only on individual methods. The `GET /inquiries` endpoint has inline role-check logic instead of using the guard.\n\n7. **Response format inconsistency**: The inquiry controller manually returns `{ message, data }` objects (skipping the TransformInterceptor), while the favorites controller returns the full `{ success, statusCode, message, data }` envelope. Tests expect the full envelope from `TransformInterceptor`.\n\n8. **No filtering/sorting/search on list endpoint**: The API doc specifies query params `status`, `propertyId`, `search`, `sortBy` for `GET /inquiries`. The current service only supports `page`/`limit` pagination.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"parentSessionId":"ses_1bc8c0c0bffeEZb75VgBylzEVF","sessionId":"ses_1bc8bc24effebujBYxTd8invt6","model":{"modelID":"deepseek-v4-pro","providerID":"opencode-go"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore inquiries module state","time":{"start":1779248151990,"end":1779248557116}},"id":"prt_e43742322001lAn4IFHqYif3tX","sessionID":"ses_1bc8c0c0bffeEZb75VgBylzEVF","messageID":"msg_e4373f914001czRTrTQoB7guc1"}}
